Claims CLAIMS  What is claimed is: 1. A system for artificial lift, said system comprising: a well casing comprising an interior surface and an exterior surface; a well head; surface production equipment; at least one pressure gauge; a hydraulic pump; an actuator housing comprising an interior surface and an exterior surface; an actuator rod housed within the actuator housing; an upper end cap comprising at least one groove, the upper end cap fixedly coupled to the actuator rod; a lower end cap fixedly coupled to the actuator rod; an inlet capillary line fixedly coupled to the upper end cap, the inlet capillary line supplying hydraulic fluid to the actuator housing; and an outlet capillary line fixedly coupled to the upper end cap, the outlet capillary line removing hydraulic fluid from the actuator housing. 2. The system of Claim 1, further comprising a spool valve, the spool valve comprising: a housing; a tri-piston assembly; at least two ports; and; 

 at least two levers, the spool valve affixed to a portion of the interior surface of the actuator rod. 3. The system of Claim 2, wherein fluid is pressurized in the inlet capillary line and outlet capillary line so as to actuate cyclical pumping movement of the spool valve to displace fluid. 4. The system of Claim 2, further comprising a stand-off affixed to the upper end cap, the stand-off engaging with the at least two levers to shift the direction of the tri-piston assembly to direct the flow of hydraulic fluid. 5. The system of Claim 1, further comprising an upper 0-ring adjacent the surface area of the upper end cap within the groove . 6. The system of Claim 1, further comprising a lower 0-ring adjacent the surface area of the lower end cap within the groove . 7. The system of Claim 1, wherein fluid is pressurized in the inlet capillary line and outlet capillary line so as to actuate cyclical pumping movement of a piston affixed to the actuator rod to displace production fluid. 8. The system of Claim 1, further comprising a piston affixed to a piston wedge affixed to the actuator rod via a plurality of extraction bolts, the piston wedge applying compression and resultant clamping forces to the actuator rod. 9. The system of Claim 1, wherein an interior portion of the actuator housing receives at least one of hydraulic fluid and gas to displace production fluid. 10. An apparatus for extracting fluid from an underground area comprising a well casing, said system comprising: an actuator housing; an actuator rod within the actuator housing; an upper end cap comprising at least one groove, the upper end cap fixedly coupled to the actuator rod; a lower end cap fixedly coupled to the actuator rod; an inlet capillary line fixedly coupled to the upper end cap, the inlet capillary line supplying hydraulic fluid to the actuator housing; and an outlet capillary line fixedly coupled to the upper end cap, the outlet capillary line removing hydraulic fluid from the actuator housing. 11. The apparatus of Claim 10, further comprising a spool valve, the spool valve comprising: a housing; a tri-piston assembly; at least two ports; and; at least two levers, the spool valve affixed to a portion of the interior surface of the actuator rod. 12. The apparatus of Claim 11, wherein fluid is pressurized in the inlet capillary line and outlet capillary line so as to 

actuate cyclical pumping movement of the spool valve to displace fluid . 13. The apparatus of Claim 11, further comprising a stand-off affixed to the upper end cap, the stand-off engaging with the at least two levers to shift the direction of the tri-piston assembly to direct the flow of hydraulic fluid. 14. The apparatus of Claim 10, further comprising an upper CD- ring adjacent the surface area of the upper end cap within the groove . 15. The apparatus of Claim 10, further comprising a lower (D-ring adjacent the surface area of the lower end cap within the groove . 16. The apparatus of Claim 10, wherein fluid is pressurized in the inlet capillary line and outlet capillary line so as to actuate cyclical pumping movement of a piston affixed to the actuator rod to displace fluid. 17. The apparatus of Claim 10, further comprising the piston affixed to a piston wedge affixed to the actuator rod via a plurality of extraction bolts, the piston wedge applying compression and resultant clamping forces to the actuator rod. 18. The apparatus of Claim 10, wherein an interior portion of the actuator housing receives at least one of hydraulic fluid and gas to displace production fluid.
